narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Yes if you have a little bit of Chinese and want to become fluent!
CHNS 142 is a solid continuation of CHNS 132. The work is slightly more challenging than CHNS 132 since CHNS 142 is much more fast-paced. However, it is a very rewarding class.

I would recommend this class to another student. This class moves faster than Chns 132, with more focus on discussions about the topics mentioned in the chapters. Students learn a lot of characters, and improve their speaking through the discussions and oral presentations.

The Chinese heritage course is a great course at Yale. I have learned so much of the course of a year. There is a lot of work each day, but the effort you put in really shows when you can write essays in Chinese and create an oral presentation about a current issue in China. I would definitely recommend this course.
